  "texts": [
    "The snapshots under microscopy were captured using a scientific imaging system (BGIMAGING C20).",
    "Additionally, WSIs were scanned at a magnification of 40× (0.20 µm pixel-1) using a digital pathology scanner (SQS120P, Shengqiang Technology).",
    "In order to maintain consistency in image size and detail resolution across different imaging modalities, patches were initially cropped from WSIs at a 2.5× magnification with dimensions of 300 × 300 pixels.",
    "For micrographs, images were originally cropped at a size of 524 × 524 pixels at the same magnification and subsequently resized to 300 × 300 pixels to ensure uniformity in resolution and compatibility across all datasets.",
    "These preprocessing steps were designed to standardize the input images for consistent analysis and fair comparison."
  ],
